This paper discusses the use of machine learning in automated decision-making systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses issues related to biases, which can be seen as a topic in both cybersecurity (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The use of value-sensitive design methodologies is also mentioned, which is a topic in social and information sciences (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses technical and emergent biases, which can be seen as a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
